The paper introduces a new classification algorithm that aims to optimize the distribution differences between classes. This falls under the category of machine learning and specifically, classification. The algorithm uses a hybrid of evolutionary strategy and Quasi-Newton method, which are optimization techniques commonly used in machine learning. The paper also experiments with linear and non-linear transformations, which are common techniques in computer vision and neural networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of multi-layer perceptrons, decision trees, and k-nearest neighbors, which are common techniques in neural networks and pattern recognition, hence, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SI (Signal and Image Processing) are also likely sub-categories.
